			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I played EQ for three years, raided most zones in the game prior to PoP, and am now trying out SB.
<br />

<br />
The lack of a first person interface is by far the hardest thing to get past in this game.  It sucks, full stop.  This is without doubt a competitive liability for SB and will continue to be so until they upgrade it.  I think anyone who played EQ will be put off by it and might junk the game immediately.  It certainly crossed my mind lol, but I am glad I stuck with it a bit longer.  I am now level 22 and have gotten better at using the interface.
<br />

<br />
The skill based character development progression in SB is superior to the EQ progression in my opinion.  A level 65 human monk in EQ is identical to any other lvl 65 monk except for the equipment and the skills of the operator.  In SB you can optimize your character to be a damage dealer type, puller type, tank type, etc. by focusing on specific skill advancements.  Your character becomes much more personalized then in EQ.
<br />

<br />
Combat in SB is similar to EQ.  There is one main difference and that is how they compute stamina.  In SB if you run out of stamina you can not run and you really can not fight at all.  Which means unless you have a lot of friends with you your going to die.  Fighting takes up stamina.  Special powers (Non caster) have a stamina cost.  Running (Pulling) requires stamina.  In SB stamina is another form of energy pool, which I think makes more sense then how they do it in EQ anyway.
<br />

<br />
The grouping experience is far superior then EQ.  Not only can you group with 10 people at a time, there is no real experience penalty to do so.  If I solo a mob I get about 5k exp.  If I group up with 10 people and kill the same mob everyone in the group will get about 4.5k of experience each.  In SB your always welcome into a group if there is an opening.  In EQ, at level 60+, getting a group can be the most time consuming and frustrating part of the game.
<br />

<br />
The end game in EQ is brutal.  With PoP you have to be in a huge guild to progress through the planes.  Most large guilds require regular raiding times which for the most part takes hours of preparation.  Its very time consuming and most of the toons are loot hungry which can cause conflict and dispute within the guild and between guilds competing for a spawn.  I have not even come close to reaching the end game with SB, but its marketed as guild level PvP.  So if another guild pisses you off, your fully expected to go to war over it.  Which sounds very cool to me.
<br />

<br />
Content wise EQ owns SB hands down.  There is no comparison.
<br />

<br />
That's my initial feedback for playing the game this weekend for any EQ fans who are considering the game.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
