			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have heard alot of people complain about the graphics of SB as compared to EQ.  In my opinion, I think that the graphics in EQ are nice, in a cartoonish kind of way for the most part.  In SB, it looks like a living painting.  The scenery is really nice, and being a person that loves RPGs (been playing them most of my life) I find that EQ can tend to be very one-tracked for its graphics.  Also, for those that think SB could have been made on a better graphic engine, think about it this way...
<br />

<br />
How many times on EQ have you walked into the bazaar with almost 200 people in it and started clipping to the point where it takes you a few seconds to take one step?  LAG CITY!  However, the graphic engine that SB is based upon is made to be able to not only have tons of people in one area, but tons on your screen as well.  In EQ on big raids, how many of us have died due to horrible lag spikes? &lt;&lt;raises his hand&gt;&gt; And in SB, I find the lag not that bad at all.  I can tolerate a little lag, but sometimes in EQ it gets so bad that it ends up killing you off.  
<br />

<br />
All in all, my point is that the graphics of this game are not the same engine as EQ because it is not EQ, and also because the EQ graphics engine could NEVER do what the SB engine does.  Frankly, for those that love graphics more than gameplay, then go play EQ, uber twink your char, and get bored by level 10 fighting the same things over and over.  For those that truly love RPGs and know that with RPGs it is the player that makes the world, not the game, try SB, you will love it!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
