				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Think of it this way, add the style of play from Diablo 2, the skills of Ultima OnLine, and add a splash of RvR from DAoC and voila! Shadowbane is created! The element of being the main character in a fantasy novel, like in EQ where everyone is a hero as long as you have the legendary loot, isn't there in SB. 
<br />

<br />
As far as someone running up against a tree until their stamina is gone sounds more like player error. When the tree is positioned between the camera and the player, or the camera is zoomed in too close, trees disappear. I see this as a way to loot corpses that might be stuck in a tree. Also think about how physical activities in real life would effect you, people tend to get winded after shouting and certainly wouldn't run so long wearing an extra 95 pounds of armor. 
<br />

<br />
The end game os SB is quite simple. There is no end game. The world will be forever changing as long as players host sieges and wage war. There are an endless possibility of scenerios for plot and content in SB like siege, war, civil war, mutiny, etc etc etc.  Unlike the sorry undeveloped world of EQ the end game seems to be the same from lvl 1 just with different mobs.    <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" /> <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
