			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">First off I have to say, anyone who thinks Everquest is full of content is full of crap! What is there in Everquest? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
As little as you may think of the content in EQ it is quite superior to a few other games I've seen including SB.
<br />

<br />
EQ has a wide variety of cities, environments and some of them have character.  Passing through Blackburrow with all its ramps and various groups of gnolls is a maze that doesn't look like many other zones in the game (maybe RunnyEye and a few others).  Then you pass into Everfrost: miles of tundra with a huge river in the middle, a barbarian city the lair of one of the fiercest dragons you would encounter until you go to Kunark or Velious.
<br />

<br />
Even if you look at the original EQ it had a wide variety of places.  Outdoor zones, cities with vendors and races of different creatures.  Dungeons with a variety of feels to them.  I'm not saying EQ doesn't have its repetitive parts.  But almost any game is repetitive.   But is there enough variety to make the repetition interesting?  In EQ I think so.  
<br />

<br />
Playing Anarchy Online there was VERY little variation in the game.  You either ran around several somewhat similar cities with similar buildings (although the layout was different wooooooo).  Or you trek across MILES of grasslands, maybe sometimes wooded areas to get to outposts or these autogenerated dungeons that looked the same after a while.  I understand they've added more dungeon types and other ways to expand the content, but I doubt they add the variety of environments as EQ has.  Stores are just kiosks.  They don't have names.  No personality.  Quest kiosks are just that: kiosks.  The quests themselves are randomly generated.  Yawn.
<br />

<br />
Shadowbane as a PvE probably isn't gonna have the variation everquest has.  Its a PvP game.  The players will shape the world.  But I doubt the world will have the kind of variety EQ has.  From what little I have seen on the newbie island the countryside looks mostly the same, the hamlets look mostly the same and so do the cities.
<br />

<br />
Izarek</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
