				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok  It seems that People have a love hate relation with EQ.   There is no doubt that you compare EQ to shadow bane.  Obviously there are differences.. No one is saying they are the same...  You would also compare asherons call and dark age of Camelot to this... these are MMRPG games... Now Because someone likes something one does better then the other does not men the other is a Bad product.   Saying EQ has had 5 years to improve on their initial release does not mean SB does not have this advantage.  SB developers have seen what has gone right and what has gone wrong with EQ  they have had 5 years so read feed back on the boards.  Thus they could tweak their product appropriately before release.  I have said Lag has been and issue and people respond like I said Lag happens 100% of the time... It is not and issue 100% of the time.  Lag does seem to get worse as I explore...  I have an arocoix and am able to get to places pretty easily.  I have not see how to swim up due to the interface and get caught drowning.   I have not been able to swim across the water with my head above it so I can breathe.  However I have been able to fly across.  But I have to wait for the world to finish loading.  My Toon stops dead in his tracks while the landscape renders.  I have seen rolling hills and ran onto them to discover the trees had not been rendered yet and when they have, I am in in the middle of a forest having to tile and turn the world so I can fin a spot to click for my guy to be able to get unstuck.   I have not been PK'd at all but have been axed plenty by groups of Mobs that I did not realize were there until the area finished loading.  then they were all around me and axed me quick.   These are frustrations.  I am not saying SB sux I am not saying EQ sux  there is no need to cut one down to defend another....</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
