			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am also coming from a couple years of EQ.  So far, I am finding SB fun and the fact that you can always get into a group (finding one can be another story) is refreshing.
<br />

<br />
The 3rd person interface is hard to get used to.  Even if I had not been used to EQ, I'd still think that SB's perspective is a bit lame.  I'm constantly messing the with the camera and accidentally bumping the side/top/bottom of the screen and causing it to move.  This, though, I think is something that I can deal with.
<br />

<br />
My one real complaint, though, is the lack of a forward/back movement key!  Only the left/right arrows do anything - the up/down are just useless.  This becomes an issue when you are in a small space with lots of other chars and it's a SERIOUS PITA to maneuver.  This also goes for moving around indoors (shops, for example, with lots of crap on the floor).  I REALLY hope they fix this one soon - it seems like it would be extremely easy for them to do and would make a world of difference in something that you're constantly using/doing.
<br />

<br />
But, I'd also throw-in a request for first-person at some  point in the future.
<br />

<br />
Mike</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
